This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with multi-target tracking, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of structured prediction and loss functions also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of contextual cues and suppression of overlapping tracks suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of dynamic programming suggests a robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as this is a common technique in robotics. Finally, the use of LP relaxation suggests a cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category, as LP is commonly used in optimization problems in cryptography.
